    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of beech tree that grows to 24 m (79 feet) in height, with divisions at the base into several stems. It is one of the primary species of deciduous forests in Japan. It is grown as an ornamental in the western hemisphere.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
